 seat on Hermann\u2019s truck available, Mouch enlists the help from Ritter. \n |LineColor = B30D0D \n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Chicago Fire (season 8)\n |EpisodeNumber = 174\n |EpisodeNumber2 = 15\n |Title = Off The Grid\n |DirectedBy = Reza Tabrizi\n |WrittenBy = Matt Whitney\n |OriginalAirDate = {{start date|2020|2|26}}\n |ProdCode = 815\n |Viewers = 8.66<ref name=\"8.15\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-wednesday-cable-originals-network-finals-2-26-2020.html|title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Wednesday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 2.26.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|date=February 27, 2020|work=Showbuzz Daily|accessdate=February 27, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary = 51 responds to a call of a group of teenagers overdosing on counterfeit heroin. Former Chicago patrol officer Sean Roman (special guest star [[Brian Geraghty]]) returns to Chicago and informs 51 that his sister is missing and was last seen at that same location. Severide begins to suspect that Roman is leading on more than what he says as he begins to search on his own. Meanwhile, Casey encourages Brett to meet her birth mother.\n----\nThe first episode of a two-part crossover that [[Chicago P.D. (season 7)#ep143|concludes on ''Chicago P.D.'']]\n |LineColor = B30D0D\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Chicago Fire (season 8)\n |EpisodeNumber = 175\n |EpisodeNumber2 = 16\n |Title = The Tendency of a Drowning Victim\n |DirectedBy = Matt Earl Beesley\n |WrittenBy = Andrea Newman & Michael Gilvary\n |OriginalAirDate = {{start date|2020|3|4}}\n |ProdCode = 816\n |Viewers = 8.26<ref name=\"8.16\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-wednesday-cable-originals-network-finals-3-4-2020.html|title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Wednesday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 3.4.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|date=March 5, 2020|work=Showbuzz Daily|accessdate=March 5, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary = 51 responds to a call where a car cras